Source: elektra
Section: base
Priority: optional 
Maintainer: Joan Valduvieco Llopart <joan@laigu.net>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5), autotools-dev, libxml2-dev, doxygen, xsltproc, docbook-xsl, libdb4.4-dev, libgconf2-dev
Standards-Version: 3.7.2

Package: libelektra
Architecture: any
Priority: optional
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libelektra-utils
Description: A framework to get system and user values
 The objective of the Elektra Project is to help create a pervasive,
 ubiquitous configuration system. This is an entire ecosystem, much
 more than a piece of code. This section lists the work of some
 people that are helping to build it.
 This package contains elektra libraries and filesys backend.

